HandlerMapping : Interface to be implemented by objects that define a mapping between and handler objects
   1.BeanNameUrlHandlerMapping
   2.RequestMappingHandlerMapping
   
HandlerExecutionChain : Handler execution chain, consisting of handler object and any handler interceptors.

HandlerAdapter : To handle the request.

Annotation : https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_annotation

@RestController 

@Requestbody 

@ResponseBody

@RequestMapping

@PostMapping

@ComponentScan

@ControllerAdivce

@Exceptionhandler

Repository steps:

1.pom.xml    +spring data jpa repositroy
2.application.porpeties   configure db info
3.create entity(@entiry, @table, @id , @column)
4.scan entity packages(@EntityScan("com.krishna"))
5. Enable jpa repositories(@EnableJpaRepositories("com.krishna.dao")
6.Implement Repository
@Repository
public interface UserRespository extends CrudRepository<User, String> 



   